-- Ontario Teachers buys Macquarie's stake in UK's Bristol Airport
-- By Esha Vaish in Bangalore
-- Wed Sep 17, 2014 06:59AM EDT
-- None



Sept 17 (Reuters) - Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan is buying out co-shareholder Australian asset manager Macquarie Group Ltd <MQG.AX> in Bristol Airport, giving the Canadian company control of UK's ninth busiest airport.

Although the companies did not disclose financial terms of the deal, a source told Reuters in July that Ontario Teachers' could spend up to 250 million pounds ($407 million) to buy Macquarie European Infrastructure Fund's 50 percent stake. [ID:nL6N0Q33FV] Bristol Airport posted a pretax profit of 25.8 million pounds in 2013.